# ChangeLog for gnome-extra/evolution-data-server
# Copyright 1999-2008 Gentoo Foundation; Distributed under the GPL v2
# $Header: $

  21 Jan 2008; Daniel Gryniewicz <dang@gentoo.org>
  evolution-data-server-2.21.5:
  Bump to 2.21.5
  	- Improved Mime header decoding (Jeffrey Stedfast)
  Bug Fixes:
  	- Do not send headers in UTF-8 (Jeffrey Stedfast)
  	- Fixed multiple password prompts in an exchange account (Sushma Rai)
  	- Get the decoded content size of a MIME part (Jean-Christophe BEGUE)
  	- Always store birthday of contact with 4-digit year and modify it
  	  according to locale setting upon display (Milan Crha)
  	- Improve SMTP error reporting (Milan Crha)
  	- Convert a g_assert to g_warning. (Sankar P)
  	- Fix a crash if the action is not recognised by soup. So if the message
  	  is null return (Srinivasa Ragavan)
  	- Check the value for NULL before comparing. (Srinivasa Ragavan)
  	- Don't pass events if the object is being destroyed. (Srinivasa Ragavan)
  	- Downsyncs all the messages from folders marked for offline use (Bharath
  	  Acharya)
  	- Handle empty strings (Srinivasa Ragavan)
  	- Remove excessive whitespace on password dialogs (Ted Percival)
  	- Do not ignore HELO failed message (Milan Crha)
  	- Fixed a crash in calendar (Ondrej Jirman)
  	- Extract error only if it is there (Srinivasa Ragavan)

